[","value":[["China"]]},".  Flight time from ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Tokyo"]]},", the busiest route, is around 90 minutes.\n\n",{"type":"===","value":["By train"]},"\nThe Sanyo Shinkansen from ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Osaka"]]}," to ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Fukuoka"]]}," (Hakata) runs down the coast of Hiroshima prefecture, stopping at all major cities including ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Hiroshima"]]}," and ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Onomichi"]]},".  Direct ",{"type":"''","value":["Nozomi"]}," trains from Tokyo take about four hours to reach Hiroshima and cost ¥18,500 one-way.\n\n",{"type":"===","value":["By bus"]},"\n\n",{"type":"==","value":["Get around"]},"\t \n\n",{"type":"==","value":["See"]},"\n",{"type":"*","value":[" View the remnants of the devastation left by the atomic bomb at the ",{"type":"'''","value":["Atomic Bomb Memorial Museum and Peace Park"]}," (",{"type":"[[","value":[["Hiroshima"]]},")"]},{"type":"*","value":[" Take a ferry to ",{"type":"'''","value":["Itsukushima Shrine"]}," the most photographed Shinto Shrine and World Heritage Site (",{"type":"[[","value":[["Miyajima"]]},")"]},{"type":"*","value":[" Try the local sake and roam the historic streets of Saijo (",{"type":"[[","value":[["Higashihiroshima"]]},")"]},{"type":"*","value":[" See the \"",{"type":"'''","value":["best view in Asia"]},"\" firsthand in Tomonoura (",{"type":"[[","value":[["Fukuyama"]]},")"]},{"type":"*","value":[" Tour the facilities of the famous Japanese car-maker at the ",{"type":"'''","value":["Mazda Museum"]}," (",{"type":"[[","value":[["Hiroshima"]]},")"]},{"type":"*","value":[" Enjoy the seasonal flowers at ",{"type":"'''","value":["Sera Kogen"]}," (",{"type":"[[","value":[["Sera"]]},")"]},"\n",{"type":"==","value":["Do"]},"\n",{"type":"===","value":["Higashi-Hiroshima City"]},"\n",{"type":"*","value":[" Saijo Sake Festival in October."]},{"type":"*","value":[" Visit a sake brewery."]},"\n",{"type":"==","value":["Eat"]},"\n",{"type":"*","value":[{"type":"{{","value":[["eat"],["name="],["url="],["email="],["address="],["lat="],["long="],["directions="],["phone="],["tollfree="],["fax="],["hours="],["price="],["content=Okonomiyaki"]]}]},{"type":"*","value":[{"type":"{{","value":[["eat"],["name="],["url="],["email="],["address="],["lat="],["long="],["directions="],["phone="],["tollfree="],["fax="],["hours="],["price="],["content=Oysters (牡蠣 or ",{"type":"''","value":["kaki"]},")"]]}]},"\n",{"type":"==","value":["Drink"]},"\t \n\n",{"type":"==","value":["Go next"]},"\t \n",{"type":"[[","value":[["Okayama Prefecture"]]}," lies to the east. ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Kurashiki"]]}," with its beautiful and well-preserved historic district is easily accessible from Hiroshima Prefecture. Other cities in the prefecture include ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Okayama"]]},", which contains many museums, ",{"type":"'''","value":["Korakuen Garden"]}," one of ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Japan's Top 3"]]}," gardens, and the ",{"type":"'''","value":["Kibi Trail"]},", among other things. The city of ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Takahashi"]]}," is home to the famous ",{"type":"'''","value":["Bitchu Matsuyama Castle"]},", which is the highest castle in Japan, as well as one of Japan's remaining original castles.\n\n",{"type":"[[","value":[["Shimane"]]}," Prefecture is located north of Hiroshima Prefecture. In ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Izumo"]]}," you can find ",{"type":"'''","value":["Izumo Shrine"]},", the second most holy Shinto Shrine in the nation; it's quite an impressive site. The city of ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Matsue"]]}," is famous for ",{"type":"'''","value":["Matsue Castle"]},", one of only twelve original castles left in Japan, ",{"type":"'''","value":["Vogel Park"]},", one of the largest greenhouses in the world, and the ",{"type":"'''","value":["Lafcadio Hearn Residence"]},". ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Shimane"]]}," is also home to one of UNESCO's World Heritage Sites, Iwami Ginzan, in ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Oda"]]},".\n\n",{"type":"[[","value":[["Yamaguchi (prefecture)"]]}," borders Hiroshima Prefecture to the west. In the city of ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Yamaguchi"]]},", you will find the beautiful ",{"type":"'''","value":["Rurikoji Temple"]},", ",{"type":"'''","value":["Joieiji Temple"]},", and memorial for ",{"type":"'''","value":["Saint Francis Xavier"]},". In ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Hagi"]]},", there are many cultural sites, such as the ruins of ",{"type":"'''","value":["Hagi Castle"]},", ",{"type":"'''","value":["Hagi Castle Town"]},", and the ",{"type":"'''","value":["Hagi Uragami Museum"]}," which houses a large amount of famous Japanese ",{"type":"'''","value":["Ukiyoe"]}," artwork. For nature lovers, ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Akiyoshidai"]]}," is home to ",{"type":"'''","value":["Akiyoshidai Plateau"]},", the largest limestone plateau in Japan and the ",{"type":"'''","value":["Akiyoshido Cave"]},", the largest cave in Japan. ",{"type":"[[","value":[["Akiyoshidai"]]}," is not so well known among foreign tourists however, it is a unique and very worthwhile addition to one's travel itinerary.\n\n",{"type":"[[","value":[["WikiPedia:Hiroshima Prefecture"]]},"\n",{"type":"[[","value":[["Dmoz:Regional\/Asia\/Japan\/Prefectures\/Hiroshima\/"]]},"\n\n",{"type":"{{","value":[["geo"],["34.4333"],["132.7500"]]},"\n\n",{"type":"{{","value":[["IsPartOf"],["Chugoku"]]},"\n",{"type":"{{","value":[["outlineregion"]]}]